column1: # This file allows to specify the default MIME type for a file type extension. The order of the the entries in this file
# determines how they are selected. Ev'ry entry in this file MUST be part of the Apache file (http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/httpd/httpd/trunk/docs/conf/mime.types).
# (Take one SPACE character as separator.) The file type extension MUST NOT contain the period (".") and should be lowercase.
# A line MUST contain exactly one MIME type and one file type extension.

column2: which begin with the '#' character are treated as comments.
